    "text": "Your sleep, not your heart, is the thing to work on here. Waking from a stress dream with a fast heartbeat is a normal adrenaline response and it settles on its own; the version worth a doctor's visit is palpitations that show up repeatedly at rest without a trigger, or with chest discomfort or lightheadedness. Your numbers look reassuringly ordinary: resting heart rate is 56 bpm, essentially identical to your 56.1 baseline, HRV is 60 ms near your 61.7 baseline, and recovery sits at 64%. Last night's 411 minutes is only a bit under your 430-minute weekly average, so this is a one-night dip, not a pattern. Two things for tonight: get to bed about 30 minutes earlier to repay the dip, and do a short screen-free wind-down before lights out so the stress carryover has somewhere to drain.",
